 Note that when answering a question, in Japanese you agree or disagree with the question rather than using an absolute positive/negative response. To illustrate:<br>
<br>
Do you have a car?<br>
English: Yes, I have a car.<br>
Japanese: Yes, I have a car.<br>
<br>
Do you not have a car?<br>
English: Yes, I have a car.<br>
Japanese: No, I have a car.<br>
